18/06/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and his Romanian counterpart, Adrian Nastase, are expected to attend weekend celebrations marking the 50th anniversary of the first Danube Bridge.
The head of the European Commission delegation to Bulgaria, Dimitris Kourkoulas, has been invited as well.
In other news, the Bulgarian government on Thursday (17 June) approved a financial agreement worth 20m euros with the German agency KfW for the construction of the second Danube Bridge.
The funding includes an 18m-euro loan and a 2m-euro grant.
(Sega - 18/06/04;
News.bg - 17/06/04)
